cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

This paper deals with a classification problem using convolutional neural networks, specifically for medical data with imbalanced number of datasets among classes. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new architecture for the CNN model, which involves aggregating outputs of multiple binary neural network models, indicating a possible fit for cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of pretrained models suggests a possible fit for cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also mentions the use of deep learning models, indicating a possible fit for cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper applies the proposed method to cataract grading, which involves image processing, suggesting a possible fit for cs.MM (Multimedia).
